PCA

. \(\mathbf{X}\in \mathrm{R}^{n\times p}\) .

\[ \mathbf{X}^\mathrm{T} = \sum_{i=1}^d\sqrt{\lambda_i}U_iV_i^\mathrm{T} = \sum_{i=1}^d F_iV_i^\mathrm{T} = \sum_{i=1}^d U_i Z_i^\mathrm{T}, \]

  1. \(U_i\) , . ;

  2. \(V_i\) , ;

  3. \(F_i\) (), \(F_i = \sqrt{\lambda_i}U_i\),

\[f_{ij} = <X_i^\mathrm{(c)},V_j > = \widehat{\text{cov}}(X_i^\mathrm{(c)},V_j) ;\]

  1. \(Z_i\) , \(z_{ij} = <\mathbf{X}^\mathrm{T}_i,U_j>\) i- \(\{U_j \}\).

:

1)pca$tab == \(\mathbf{X}^\mathrm{(s)}\), ;

2)pca$li == \(\mathbf{Z}\), ;

3)pca$l1 == \(\mathbf{V}\), ;

4)pca$co == \(\mathbf{F}\), ;

5)pca$c1 == \(\mathbf{U}\), .

get_pca_var .

  1. $coord , \(\mathbf{F}\), ;

  2. $cor , $coord;

  3. $cos2 \(\cos^2(X_i,V_j)\), \(\{f_{ij}^2\}\);

  4. $contrib \(\cos^2\) i- j-

\[\text{contrib}_{ij}=100\dfrac{\cos^2(X_i,V_j)}{\sum_{k=1}^p \cos^2(X_k,V_j)} .\]
